summary: I hate how people treats Arya’s traumas and pain as something glorious, like yes she is fucking strong for handeling all of that...
body:
I hate how people treats Arya’s traumas and pain as something glorious, like yes she is fucking strong for handeling all of that shit, but still she is not invencible, she is human, a traumatized kid that lost everything, and that is not something to glorify. During seven/eighth season the writers treat her like a kill machines who has no feelings and is able to kill her own sister, one of the only persons she has left, like, she doesn’t care, she has no feelings, because she is a strong female character and strong famale characters can’t have feelings, or feel vulnerable, or sad, or dealing with her traumas and pains for real, acording to them.

I have to give congratulations to maise Williams to make an amazing performance with such an superficial script, she gave her best to not make Arya looking like a killing machine, she is a great actress

title:

        Archive of Our Own
excerpt: An Archive of Our Own, a project of the Organization for Transformative Works
description:
summary

None of it’s worked out how he thought it would: he’s in love, but she won’t marry him. He’s legitimized, but none of his family’s alive. He’s a Lord, but he doesn’t know how to read or write. And now he’s a Baratheon. One allied to the Targaryen Queen who just brought all of King’s Landing to the ground.

Above everything, Gendry needs help.
One day, it rides in on a white horse.

chapter 13: forest lass

People will eventually call this night the White Wedding. Gendry figures it’s because white’s the color for surrender.

❤ ❤ ❤ ❤ ❤ ❤ ❤ ❤

We don’t need to have just one favorite. We keep adding favorites. Our favorite book is always the book that speaks most directly to us at a particular stage in our lives. And our lives change. We have other favorites that give us what we most need at that particular time. But we never lose the old favorites. They’re always with us. We just sort of accumulate them.

summary: “Whatever you feel for me is dangerous. I’m dangerous. Us, together? Dangerous.”
title: “Whatever you feel for me is dangerous. I’m dangerous. Us, together? Dangerous.”
body:
You were just a common girl.

You weren’t a lady nor a knight just a common girl.

And you were in love with Arya.

And she was in love with you.

You expected it one day but it still hurts. “Whatever you feel for me is dangerous”, she told you one day when she was ready to leave Winterfell. “I’m dangerous”, Arya said to you as well to herself. “Us…together?”, She trailed off than ended it, “Dangerous”. You gave a crooked smile, “I understand” was all you said seeing her confusion before turning away from her knowing she’ll come back when the battle is over.

summary: Game of Thrones | Fã reescreve final e viraliza
title: Game of Thrones | Fã reescreve final e viraliza
body:
Game of Thrones | Fã reescreve final e viraliza

Wow, um fã decidiu refazer, da sua maneira, a oitava temporada de Game of Thrones, modificando, assim, o final da série. O vídeo com a ideia foi publicado no final de maio e já conta com mais de quatro milhões de visualizações. 

A grande diferença da trama proposta pelo fã Daniel Whidden, do Think Story, é a participação do Rei da Noite nos capítulos finais. Vale notar que Whidden não mudaria…
